441 typedef struct shader_s {
442  char name[MAX_QPATH]; // game path, including extension
443  int lightmapIndex; // for a shader to match, both name and lightmapIndex must match
444 
445  int index; // this shader == tr.shaders[index]
446  int sortedIndex; // this shader == tr.sortedShaders[sortedIndex]
447 
448  float sort; // lower numbered shaders draw before higher numbered
449 
450  qboolean defaultShader; // we want to return index 0 if the shader failed to
451  // load for some reason, but R_FindShader should
452  // still keep a name allocated for it, so if
453  // something calls RE_RegisterShader again with
454  // the same name, we don't try looking for it again
455 
456  qboolean explicitlyDefined; // found in a .shader file
457 
458  int surfaceFlags; // if explicitlyDefined, this will have SURF_* flags
459  int contentFlags;
460 
461  qboolean entityMergable; // merge across entites optimizable (smoke, blood)
462 
463  qboolean isSky;
464  skyParms_t sky;
465  fogParms_t fogParms;
466 
467  float portalRange; // distance to fog out at
468  qboolean isPortal;
469 
470  cullType_t cullType; // CT_FRONT_SIDED, CT_BACK_SIDED, or CT_TWO_SIDED
471  qboolean polygonOffset; // set for decals and other items that must be offset
472  qboolean noMipMaps; // for console fonts, 2D elements, etc.
473  qboolean noPicMip; // for images that must always be full resolution
474 
475  fogPass_t fogPass; // draw a blended pass, possibly with depth test equals
476 
477  int vertexAttribs; // not all shaders will need all data to be gathered
478 
479  int numDeforms;
480  deformStage_t deforms[MAX_SHADER_DEFORMS];
481 
482  int numUnfoggedPasses;
483  shaderStage_t *stages[MAX_SHADER_STAGES];
484 
485  void (*optimalStageIteratorFunc)( void );
486 
487  double clampTime; // time this shader is clamped to
488  double timeOffset; // current time offset for this shader
489 
490  struct shader_s *remappedShader; // current shader this one is remapped too
491 
492  struct shader_s *next;
493 } shader_t;

1309 /*
1310 
1311 the drawsurf sort data is packed into a single 32 bit value so it can be
1312 compared quickly during the qsorting process
1313 
1314 the bits are allocated as follows:
1315 
1316 0 - 1 : dlightmap index
1317 //2 : used to be clipped flag REMOVED - 03.21.00 rad
1318 2 - 6 : fog index
1319 11 - 20 : entity index
1320 21 - 31 : sorted shader index
1321 
1322  TTimo - 1.32
1323 0-1 : dlightmap index
1324 2-6 : fog index
1325 7-16 : entity index
1326 17-30 : sorted shader index
1327 
1328  SmileTheory - for pshadows
1329 17-31 : sorted shader index
1330 7-16 : entity index
1331 2-6 : fog index
1332 1 : pshadow flag
1333 0 : dlight flag
1334 */
1335 #define QSORT_FOGNUM_SHIFT 2
1336 #define QSORT_REFENTITYNUM_SHIFT 7
1337 #define QSORT_SHADERNUM_SHIFT (QSORT_REFENTITYNUM_SHIFT+REFENTITYNUM_BITS)
1338 #if (QSORT_SHADERNUM_SHIFT+SHADERNUM_BITS) > 32

1832 static ID_INLINE qboolean ShaderRequiresCPUDeforms(const shader_t * shader)
1833 {
1834  if(shader->numDeforms)
1835  {
1836  const deformStage_t *ds = &shader->deforms[0];
1837 
1838  if (shader->numDeforms > 1)
1839  return qtrue;
1840 
1841  switch (ds->deformation)
1842  {
1843  case DEFORM_WAVE:
1844  case DEFORM_BULGE:
1845  // need CPU deforms at high level-times to avoid floating point percision loss
1846  return ( backEnd.refdef.floatTime != (float)backEnd.refdef.floatTime );
1847 
1848  default:
1849  return qtrue;
1850  }
1851  }
1852 
1853  return qfalse;
1854 }
